//[Reference] 'It feels good to patrol the village every day.'
staxel.village.dialogue.job.Sweeper.line:10000100=È bello pattugliare il villaggio ogni giorno.
//[Reference] 'I'm the one keeping our streets clean!'
staxel.village.dialogue.job.Sweeper.line:10000200=Sono io che pulisco le nostre strade!
//[Reference] 'It's becoming harder and harder to find a place to store my ^c:d03e37;brooms^c:pop;.'
staxel.village.dialogue.job.Sweeper.line:10000300=Sta diventando difficile trovare un posto dove posare le mie ^c:d03e37;scope^c:pop;.
//[Reference] 'I think I'm going to have to install a few more racks...'
staxel.village.dialogue.job.Sweeper.line:10000400=Penso che dovrò installare altri armadietti...
//[Reference] 'What I wouldn't give for an Arcus 2001...'
staxel.village.dialogue.job.Sweeper.line:10000500=Cosa non darei per un Arcus 2001...
//[Reference] 'The sweeping action is said to be divine.'
staxel.village.dialogue.job.Sweeper.line:10000600=Si dice che sia divina
//[Reference] 'I hear nothing can clean a street even half as well.'
staxel.village.dialogue.job.Sweeper.line:10000700=Sento che nulla può pulire una strada neanche per la metà.
//[Reference] 'Someone keeps vandalising the town hall's signboard...'
staxel.village.dialogue.job.Sweeper.line:10000800=Qualcuno continua a vandalizzare l'insegna del municipio...
//[Reference] 'They plaster it with posters of infuriatingly adorable kittens.'
staxel.village.dialogue.job.Sweeper.line:10000900=Lo tappezzano con poster di gattini adorabilmente infuriati.
//[Reference] 'I'll bet my broom that it's ^c:1486b0;{0-tomboy_name}^c:pop;.'
staxel.village.dialogue.job.Sweeper.line:10001000=Scommetto che è la mia scopa ^c:1486b0;{0-tomboy_name}^c:pop;.
//[Reference] 'Someday I'll get myself an auto-cleaner.'
staxel.village.dialogue.job.Sweeper.line:10001100=Un giorno mi farò un robot che pulisce.
//[Reference] 'It wouldn't be anywhere near as effective as I am...'
staxel.village.dialogue.job.Sweeper.line:10001200=Non sarebbe efficiente quanto me...
//[Reference] 'But at least it would decrease my workload.'
staxel.village.dialogue.job.Sweeper.line:10001300=Ma almeno ridurrebbe il mio carico di lavoro.
//[Reference] 'Maybe I could convince ^c:1486b0;{0-scientist_name}^c:pop; to build me one?'
staxel.village.dialogue.job.Sweeper.line:10001400=Forse potrei convincere ^c:1486b0;{0-scientist_name}^c:pop; a costruirmene uno
//[Reference] 'Feel free to give me a hand whenever you're free.'
staxel.village.dialogue.job.Sweeper.line:10001500=Sentiti libero di darmi una mano ogni volta che sei libero.
//[Reference] 'Pick up a ^c:d03e37;broom^c:pop; and you can use it to push dropped items around!'
staxel.village.dialogue.job.Sweeper.line:10001600=Prendi una ^c:d03e37;scopa^c:pop; e puoi usarla per spingere gli oggetti caduti in giro!
//[Reference] 'It's an effective way to clean up any mess you make!'
staxel.village.dialogue.job.Sweeper.line:10001700=È un modo efficace per ripulire qualsiasi casino tu faccia!
//[Reference] '^c:1486b0;{0-playername}^c:pop;, just a word of warning.'
staxel.village.dialogue.job.Sweeper.line:10001800=^c:1486b0;{0-playername}^c:pop;, solo alcune parole di avvertimento.
//[Reference] 'Please keep your animals out of the ^c:1486b0;village square^c:pop;.'
staxel.village.dialogue.job.Sweeper.line:10001900=Si prega di tenere i vostri animali fuori dalla ^c:1486b0;piazza^c:pop;.
//[Reference] 'I have no interest in cleaning up after them.'
staxel.village.dialogue.job.Sweeper.line:10002000=Non ho alcun interesse a ripulire dopo di loro.
//[Reference] 'Sometimes I'm overcome by an inexorable need to sweep a chimney.'
staxel.village.dialogue.job.Sweeper.line:10002100=A volte sono sopraffatto da un inesorabile bisogno di spazzare un camino.
//[Reference] 'Unfortunately, we don't have many chimneys around here...'
staxel.village.dialogue.job.Sweeper.line:10002200=Sfortunatamente, non abbiamo molti camini da queste parti...
